 Following up on the song
<https://open.spotify.com/track/2waAug1IePTKYs2KhTCYlc?si=3D4f50c0a756354e7=
6>
I shared yesterday, passed to me by a friend of a friend. Turns out, it's a
"matt radosevich song" in more ways than I realized:

   - Listen close to the backing vocals. One of them is Catherine Irwin,
   i.e. half of Freakwater
   <https://open.spotify.com/artist/6JjE9yVvCNV5EbUpvS7JcQ?si=3Dec323f9a99b=
e46e2>
   (#24 and #132).
   - The record label is Sophomore Lounge
   <https://sophomoreloungerecords.com/>. Ought to be familiar to the
   Burlington concert crew:

[image: Screenshot 2025-05-08 084632.png]

Makes sense. These guys were opening
<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Dh9AhS1W6p8I>* for Lenderman on the fall
'24 tour.

That's all for now. Seemed worth sharing. Ground floor stuff.
_____________________________

Song #364: "Your Still Standin' There"
<https://open.spotify.com/track/4sD5C8vtuPtblOYanu3jSc?si=3D49962da6290e4b1=
6>
[sic]

Who Made it: Steve Earle & Lucinda Williams

Year: 1996

_______________________________

Thoughts: For a while, I had this slated as the year's last song. It's what
I had in mind on #1 when I promised something that would "mirror ["RotGA"]
in form and content" for the finale.


That much is true: instead of Emmylou and Gram, we have Lucinda and Steve.
Instead of '*twenty-thousand roads*', it's '*a thousand trails*'.


The arc is much the same:



*Oh, and I remembered something you once told meAnd I'll be damned if it
did not come true*

*Twenty thousand roads I went down, down, downAnd they all lead me straight
back home to you *("RotGA")




*And the world keeps turning 'round and 'roundIt leaves me hanging in the
airMy heart keeps turning upside downAnd you're still standin' there
*("Standin'
There")


Make the sounds of *'down, down, down'* v. *'round and round'*.

*******************

Why'd I change my mind? Why isn't this one the closer?

Too final. Too triumphant. Baller Ball told me not to overwrite my endings,
and I mean to take his advice.

Expect less next, and more to ponder.

=E2=80=93Matt


PS: Writing this last bit around 10:45 pm. The folks are in town for a
visit. I met up with them for dinner, then walked them back to their hotel.


After that, all kinds of crap** broke loose. Houston did its best to cut
the list short by setting a severe thunderstorm on me during my bike ride
home. Flash-bang thunder, blow-down wind, standing water =E2=80=94 the work=
s. Don't
tell Dan and Julie, but I almost got smacked (inches of separation) by some
numb-nut double-dipping the four-way at Woodhead and Welch. I fish-tailed,
took the lord's name, then recovered and continued.


I will not be denied: unless the night smites me, we'll have our last song.


*Worth a click for anyone who likes Zevon, cowbell, or fitting loads of
people on a stage.


**After I made it home and stripped off my wet stuff, I found a *large
*insectoid
invader =E2=80=94 not much risk of injury, but significant insult to spirit=
. I
chased it around *au naturel*, shoe-in*-*hand*, *until a blow landed.


Pray for a pestless tomorrow.


